{
  "texts": [
    "Figure 5 presents the pipeline of deploying the fine-tuned Llama3 8B for crash causation.",
    "The crash factors imported from Signal4Analytics and RITIS are combined into one full-text representation, which is then be tokenized, as LLMs operate on words as tokens.",
    "Tokenization is the process of breaking down a text sequence into smaller units, called tokens, which can be words, sub words, or characters.",
    "In the context of Natural Language Processing (NLP), tokenization is crucial as it transforms raw text into a format that machine learning models, especially LLMs, can process (56) (57) (58).",
    "It enables these models to understand and generate text by converting input data into manageable and standardized units."
  ]
}